kay, so here's my fun schedule for the next week of things that are due. not things to DO, but things that are DUE. this is why i'm posting instead of doing my DUE list. haha. that was confusing. 

- march 12 - mon - 147 hw
- march 12 - mon - 156 lab #3
- march 12 - mon - 156 hw #3
- march 14- wed - 147 project
- march 15 - thurs - 10 hw
- march 15 - thurs - 10 extra credit
- march 16 - fri - 156 hw #4
- march 16 - fri - 130 hw
- march 16 - fri - 130 project
- march 19 - mon - 156 quiz #3
- march 19 - 156 lab #4


other than those things that are DUE, i have the things to DO. . . reviews, classes, group meetings for projects, etc. weeee. 


1. Can you cook? to an extent. i don't really burn anything, and i can follow recipes perfectly fine. . . i'm just not so creative if i have to throw together something. 
2. What was your dream growing up? i wanted to do something in the "industry". i went through the phase of wanting/doing dancing, singing, and guitar/other instruments. . . but i also didn't really want to be in the spotlight, so i wanted to do something behind the scenes. i don't really know what i wanted. haha.
3. What talent do you wish you had? singing. dancing. the latter i know i could be good at if i practiced. cause i was good. . . . until i stopped in middle school and haven't really done any of it since. :p 
4. Favorite place? the place doesn't matter as much as the person i'm with. or, depends on my mood or what i want to do. 
5. Favorite vegetable? hmmmm. . . .zucchini is yummy if it's cooked right. 
6. What was the last book you read? . . . . my vibrations book earlier this evening? that's what made me start thins thing. haha. if you mean novel, i was reading Dan Brown's Angels and Demons, but didn't get to finish cause school started and i had to start reading my text books. :p i hate having to put a book down for a long time, which is why i don't read novels often unless i have a really good chunk of time *like our breaks from school* where i can read the whole thing. i like having the option of continuing if i get to a really good part. 
7. What zodiac sign are you? scorpio.
8. Any Tattoos and/or Piercings? pierced ears. probably will get a navel piercing soon. i think spring is a good time to get it done, so i can wear loose clothing while it's healing.
9. Worst Habit? as of late, i've picked up picking/biting my hangnails. it's really gross, and i never used to do it. but sometimes i really get that bored in class. . . . .or i look for split ends in my hair. LOL. oi.
10. Do we know each other outside of Livejournal? yesum. but only since 6th grade. :) 
11. What is your favorite sport? to watch. . . . probably football if i had to pick. but i don't really watch anything when i'm in irvine cause i dont have any teams to root for and then it's not as fun. but at home i like watching and i just root for whatever teams my brothers want to win. :) playing. . . or i should say "playing" would be just running or swimming. 
12. Do you have a Negative or Optimistic attitude? more negative as of late. 
13. What would you do if you were stuck in an elevator with me? oh, we'd find a LOT to do. . . haha. and just talk. cause we seem to be good at that. talk/complain. :D
14. Worst thing to ever happen to you? uhhhhhhhhhhh
15. Tell me one weird fact about you. i can spread all of my toes out in a way that, apparently, no one else i know of can. and my pinky toe can wiggle independently. hahaha. 
17. Do you know how to do the Macarena? i think i can recall it if i tried. but i really don't want to. 
18. What time is it where you are now? 11:29.
19. Do you think clowns are cute or scary? i'm impartial.
20. If you could change one thing about how you look, what would it be? i'd wish to be able to keep my body when i'm "fit" and not have to do the whole upkeep thing. hahahaha. if i had to pick a specific feature to change, i think i'd say i'd want longer legs. 
21. Would you be my partner in crime or my conscience? depends. i can be both. :) hahaha
22. What color eyes do you have? brown. randy says they're "poo brown".
23. Ever been arrested? nope
24. Bottle or Draft? wouldn't know
25. If you won $10,000 dollars today, what would you do with it? spend some, save some. 
26. What kind of bubble gum do you prefer to chew? orbit?
27. What's your favorite bar to hang at? don't have one.
28. Do you believe in ghosts? sometimes yes, sometimes no. 
29. Favorite thing to do in your spare time? uhhhhhhhhh. . . . depends?
30. Do you swear a lot? not really.
31. Biggest pet peeve? ummm. . .can i just say  "roommates"? 
32. In one word, how would you describe yourself? boring. 
33. In one word, how would you describe me? unique
34. Will you repost this so I can fill it out and do the same for you? well, this is kind of posted, so yes? fill it out for meeeeee

so, i'm actually updating this. i don't know why, i just felt like doing something with my lj. i changed up my info a tiny bit just to make it a little more current. i realized that it might be a good idea when i saw that it still said my sn was "bugiemu" and my e-mail addy was "lelopples@aol.com". i'm surprised it didn't go as far back as meowinz@aol. lol. ah, my random screennames and such. :p well, things are coming up quickly, and i'm starting to get scared about the testing and stuff. this determines everything coming up for me. and i haven't studied as well as i should have been. and i keep telling myself that i'll buckle down, and when i get to irvine, i'll have a full 11 days to just study because there's not much else for me to do anyways. but still. i have to study more now too. it's not too hard to relearn, but i'm not going to know it if i don't take a look at it. i have to start taking control of things. get off my lazy butt. there's so many things i should do before i go, so many things that seem to need to be done, but none of it really seems important for some reason. example, getting my watch battery changed and the band adjusted. if i can find the watch, now that i think about it. i don't even know where i put it. sometimes i think i'm not going to be able to make that transition that i want to into a hard worker.

YOU ARE WATER!

Your inner element is one of great compassion and
love. You are an extremely kind-hearted person
who tends to care more about helping others
than themselves at times. You gravitate to
people who need help or just a shoulder to cry
on and you provide them with the support they
need. You harbor an intense compassion for
others that is truly admirable. You are an
incredibly easy-going person who just goes with
the flow and tries to be comfortable no matter
what. You tend to collect things, little
reminders or memories of time gone past. Any
career that will allow you to help others in
any way is ideal for you. Love is a essential
element in your life, and your search for the
one and only for you is paramount to all
things. The one you choose with have to be
loyal, honest, and able to share their emotions
with you.
Your greatest strengths are your ability to bond
with others and help them through the tough
times. Your weaknesses are your tendency to get
overly emotional on things and drive those you
care about away with your emotional outbursts.
Balancing your strengths and weaknesses is
crucial for you to achieve balance in your
life.
Astrologically, Water is associated with the signs
of Cancer, Scorpio and Pisces. You are most
compatible for either love or friendship with
another Water Elemental or with an Earth. You
are least compatible with a Fire Elemental.

Parents sure can ruin a good mood. no elaboration. just thought I'd let that out. Something I'm sure the entire teenage population has already concluded. ah well, it must be said again; I don't think everyone has grasped the concept yet. Parents sure can ruin a good mood. 'Nuff said.

awww, Footloose is over. . . .it was fun, and it turned out pretty good *kind of*. we all had our doubts. . . but it worked *again. . .kind of.*! hehe. i mean, taking into account how little time we really did it in and everything. . . how long did we work on it? a whole. . . 2 months or something. how sad. fun stuff though, i'm gonna miss it. i'm all bruised because i'm so damn clumsy and was bumping into things while moving a bunch of stuff around backstage *being stage crew and all* and scratched up from the bales of hay. . . but it's all in good fun. :) hehe. you know, in the past 2 weeks, i had gotten a max of 5 hours of sleep, so you can guess what i was like today. . . i slept in until 2:00. wow. that was a first. before than, the latest i'd slept in was about. . .11 or 11:30ish. i didn't think it was possible to sleep that late. but i did it. hehe. but it was a good tired. i loved it. i'm gonna miss it. and it's sad, because i know next year i'm not going to be able to have the same opportunity. like, last year, when the play was over, i was like. . . next year i am DEFINITELY going to do it again. but i can't. :( not with these people at least. *sniff* i'm gonna miss them all!!!

everyone was sooo good, especially the friday night show! it was an almost flawless performance. loved it! even if we didn't have the spotlight! haha, who needs it! *we were thinking of just getting a huge flashlight. . . or a bunch of small ones. . . buuut, it's okay, it worked without it. :)* band, sounded great too, mikes. . .MUCH better than the day before. and then the gunderson cast was there last night. they LOVED natasha *props to her!* very cool. 

i could talk for a loooong time about the show. but so i don't make you fall asleep, i'll just put it as simply as possible. it was GREAT! hehe. i was happy. 

after the show, however, i didn't end up going to the cast party. :p oh well. i was SUPPOSED to go with my friends out to eat. .. but of course, like always, everyone that was supposed to come flaked out except for vivien. it was cool though. 

i loved last night!!! okay, i'll stop talking. hehe. but it's just like, THATS the kind of stuff i love. this is why i don't care about school as much, cuase i want THIS. i don't want to be sitting at a desk punching out numbers. . .*stupid integrals and derivative crap*. . .i want to be up, actually DOING stuff.

anyways, just a little synopsis of what went on last night. fun fun.

dah! of course, i decide to write instead of doing my homework. . .kristen's fault! she inspired me to write! 

today has been good and bad. i just feel so. . .mixed up right now. school was just school. after school was cool though. right after, mike and cindy came over cause we needed to do our stock project for tomorrow *of course, we have to wait until the last minute, right?* so, they were supposed to leave by 6, cause i needed to eat, shower, print the program, burn 3 CD's, pick 3 people up, and get to school, by 7. they didn't leave until 6:20. . .sooo, rushing!! i ended up not eating, printing the program, or burning the CD's. . . and i have to say i had a half-assed shower. me thinks i need to shower again. i feel dirty again. :p lol. ah well. i like the hectic-ness. i don't know, it makes me feel. . . accomplished. . .*not quite sure if that was the best word choice* i guess. it feels good to be busy. especially when it's doing things you like. i liked rehearsals because we actually did stuff too. yay. and i know what i'm doing now. hehe, annnnd, i found out how to use the lights. yay! cool cool. like i said already, i love being busy with things i love doing. 

it annoys me that some people don't take pride in the muscial. it's like, you signed up, do it right. and then they still fish for the credit. it annoys me so much! *kristen, you know what i'm talking about. . .you were there tonight!. . .and then the whole OTHER thing too* i swear, i just wanted to scream! i have never felt so peeved off at a stupid thing. it's like, why not? what are you doing here if you don't want to be here? i hate that people keep saying that they want to drop the class, that it's boring. . then, when something fun comes up, all of a sudden, they love it. see, there's the people like that, and then there's the other type of person. the type of person who knows that there are parts where it isn't that fun, it's pretty boring, but once you get into it, that's the best thing. i've LOVED this week because of rehearsals. it feels good to be doing this kind of thing again. 

i mean, i know i don't have that big of a part. i'm only stage crew after all. but still, i think i do my share. i figured out when the curtains need to close, which curtains, what needs to be set up and when. . . helped hala with the lights *a LITTLE bit. . .only a tad!!!*, and i'm doing the program with ewusi. *props to her for making the cover!* so yah. i duno, i think it's going okay overall. a lot better than what i expected. of course, there are still a few people who don't really want to be there be there. it's like they aren't in it for the fun, and they don't have the same passion for it. and it's just like, why are they here, why are they trying to take over my job when they don't even want it? there's no point in trying to take it away. just for the sake of having it, or what? 

sorry, i'm just blabbing on about nothing. it's really nothing important. i don't think it's something i should even be getting worked up over. but it still bugs me. especially with what we talked about kristen. see, now you can empathize instead of sympathize. you understand. :p i hate it!

but other then that stupid stuff, everything's been cool. i guess i just feel kind of possessive over it all. :p

Drr. . . stupid program isn't working for me!!! i can't space them right and stuff. . .this might take a lot longer than i thought!!! damn!

well, i guess i better go. . .actually DO my homework. . .oops. haha. that. ugh. i'll write more later.

*of course instead of doing homework after rehearsals, i decide to go somewhere. smart me. :p*

i really shouldn't be writing right now. i have so much work to do still. . . oh well. i'll make it short. 

a warning. this is a pretty personal entry. so if you don't want to get inside my head, or be confused, or what-not i suggest not reading it. in fact, i just suggest to everyone to not read it. but you know, it's really up to you. it's out there. you make the choice.

the past few weeks have kind of sucked. all school aspects at least. all this crap is going on, which i will not get into detail about, and i just feel like i'm losing it. i don't think i can stand it much longer unless i have a break. weekends are such a relief now, it's the only time i get away from the stress, but it isn't long enough. it goes SO fast, and even as early as the end of monday, i'm already longing for another weekend. it isn't really school work and stress type stuff. i don't really know what it is. it's just me. i don't feel motivated for school. it's like i'm in a rut, and am so overwhelmed that i don't even know where to start in order to get out. it doesn't feel like i ever will.

of course, there are times when i feel relief from it all. certain people can help make the feeling go away. but it's all just temporary, a quick fix. as soon as they're gone, the feeling comes flooding back. Unfortunately, there are only a couple people who can do this, and they are the people i don't get to see as often. 

one of them knows who they are, i talked to them earlier tonight. i just want to say thanks for everything. i don't mean to get all sappy, but you're my support right now. there aren't many people i can trust in every possible way, but you are one of them. it's like. . .for lack of a better metaphor, if i fall down into a group of "friends", you would be the only one to care. everyone else would look up casually and see me fall, but you would be the one running to catch me and make sure i'm okay. i love that you help me without holding my hand every step of the way. you know the difference between sympathy and empathy, and you don't try to empathize when you know you can't. if you don't understand what i'm going though *which isn't often!* then you don't act like you know. you aren't fake. you don't lie to me. you don't try to gain trust without giving trust in return. you know how to be a true friend. i feel like i can open my entire soul up to you, and you wouldn't tell a single living being about the secrets that i hold. you wouldn't even think about doing such a thing. thanks again for everything.

However, some other people have been disappointing me. it isn't a certain incident or anything, it's just an overall feeling. i don't know how much friendship really means to them. i don't know how much i can trust them. i hesitate to let them in, and there are certain things that i want to keep from them. with these people, i feel that there are things that are too personal to share with them. i feel this way because i always have a doubt about them in the back of my mind. i don't know why, i just do. i just don't feel the sincerity in their friendship and their words. they'll say one thing, and act on another. but by feeling this way, i just feel so untrustworthy. If I can't trust them, why should they trust me? shouldn't i being giving them the benefit of the doubt? i mean, they're my friends. i don't know. . .
